{"ingredients":["¼ tsp salt","½ tsp coriander seeds","½ tsp chilli flakes","1 cardamom pod","1 tsp olive oil","½ duck breast, skin on","½ large potato, peeled and sliced into 3 rounds","1 tbsp olive oil","salt and freshly ground black pepper","1 orange, zest and juice","2 tsp red wine vinegar","¼ tsp ground turmeric","1 tsp caster sugar","2 tbsp olive oil"],"method":["For the duck, place the salt, coriander seeds, chilli flakes and cardamom pod into a mortar and pestle and pound together. Stir in the oil to make a paste. Rub the spice paste all over the duck.","Heat a frying pan and fry the duck breast skin-side down for 8-10 minutes, or until a lot of the fat has been released and the skin is golden-brown and crisp.  Drain off any excess fat into a bowl.","Turn over and fry for a further 3-4 minutes, or until completely cooked through. Remove from the pan and leave to rest for five minutes in a warm place.","For the potato galette, boil the potatoes in a saucepan of salted water for five minutes, then drain.","Heat the oil in a frying pan and fry the potato slices until golden-brown.  Season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.","For the vinaigrette, heat the orange zest and juice, vinegar, turmeric and sugar in a small pan and simmer until reduced by half and syrupy. Remove from the heat and whisk in the olive oil.","To serve, arrange the potato slices on a serving plate, top with the duck and drizzle over the vinaigrette."],"url":"www_bbc_co_uk_food_recipes_sweetandspicyduckwit_87237","title":"Sweet and spicy duck with potato galette and orange vinaigrette","time":{"preparation":"less than 30 mins","preparationMins":30,"cooking":"10 to 30 mins","cookingMins":30,"totalMins":60},"serves":"Serves 1","image":"https://food.files.bbci.co.uk/kandl-food/1911/images/bbc_placeholder.png","isVegetarian":false,"recommendations":0}
