an pan, add salt and pepper to taste and set aside. ","Blanch the samphire in a large saucepan of boiling water for a minute then drain.","Heat another frying pan until hot, add the remaining butter, chanterelles and samphire. Fry over a high heat until the samphire is just wilted, but still bright green. Season with a little salt and black pepper.","To serve, pile the squash into the centre of serving bowls and top with a turbot fillet, skin-side up. Spoon the Processco sauce over the top and garnish with the mushrooms, samphire, chervil and fresh truffle."],"url":"www_bbc_co_uk_food_recipes_turbot_with_prosecco_98770","title":"Turbot with Prosecco sauce, chanterelle mushrooms, roasted squash and samphire","time":{"preparation":"30 mins to 1 hour","preparationMins":60,"cooking":"10 to 30 mins","cookingMins":30,"totalMins":90},"serves":"Serves 4","image":"https://food.files.bbci.co.uk/kandl-food/1911/images/bbc_placeholder.png","isVegetarian":false,"recommendations":0}
