if required. When the custards are cooked, set aside to cool slightly.","For the vegetable medley, preheat the oven to 220C/425F/Gas 7.\r\n\r\n","Place the pancetta between two baking trays that fit together and bake in the oven for 5-6 minutes, or until crisp. Remove from the oven and allow to cool with the baking tray on top so the pancetta stays straight.","Heat a large frying pan and add the olive oil. Once hot, add the courgette, mangetout, asparagus, girolles and peas and cook them (without colouring) until they are tender.","Place the parmesan and plain flour in a bowl and mix. To make a parmesan crisp, heat a frying pan and sprinkle a quarter of the mixture in a neat line. When the mixture starts to bubble, remove from the pan in one piece and place over a rolling pin to curve the parmesan crisp. Repeat with the remaining mixture.","To serve, add a spoonful of warm chicken jus to the custards. Place the vegetables and a slice of pancetta on top of the custards with a parmesan crisp."],"url":"www_bbc_co_uk_food_recipes_umami_bomb_parmesan_and_62918","title":"Umami bomb (parmesan and wild mushroom custard)","time":{"preparation":"less than 30 mins","preparationMins":30,"cooking":"30 mins to 1 hour","cookingMins":60,"totalMins":90},"serves":"Serves 4","image":"https://food.files.bbci.co.uk/kandl-food/1911/images/bbc_placeholder.png","isVegetarian":false,"recommendations":0}
